<P>About this time arrived Colonel Morden, the tru&s;tee for her grandfather's e&s;tate, who was received by the family with great marks of re&s;pect; but having a &s;incere regard for Clari&s;&s;a, whom he had not &s;een for &s;ome years, he re&s;olved to take his own m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">a&s;ures, to oblige Lovelace to marry her, and to put her in po&s;&s;e&s;&s;ion of her grandfather's
